		<segment id="2" parent="15" relname="span">worship of ancient Greek deities is legal</segment>
		<segment id="3" parent="18" relname="context-circumstance">Monday , March 27 , 2006</segment>
		<segment id="4" parent="5" relname="attribution-positive">Greek court has ruled</segment>
		<segment id="5" parent="19" relname="span">that worshippers of the ancient Greek religion may now formally associate and worship at archeological sites .</segment>
		<segment id="6" parent="22" relname="span">Prior to the ruling , the religion was banned from conducting public worship at archeological sites by the Greek Ministry of Culture .</segment>
		<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="causal-result">Due to that , the religion was relatively secretive .</segment>
		<segment id="8" parent="22" relname="context-background">The Greek Orthodox Church , a Christian denomination , is extremely critical of worshippers of the ancient deities .</segment>
		<segment id="9" parent="24" relname="span">Today , about 100,000 Greeks worship the ancient gods , such as Zeus , Hera , Poseidon , Aphrodite , and Athena .</segment>
		<segment id="10" parent="11" relname="attribution-positive">The Greek Orthodox Church estimates</segment>
		<segment id="11" parent="25" relname="span">that number is closer to 40,000 .</segment>
		<segment id="12" parent="26" relname="adversative-contrast">Many neo - pagan religions , such as Wicca , use aspects of ancient Greek religions in their practice ;</segment>
		<segment id="13" parent="27" relname="span">Hellenic polytheism instead focuses exclusively on the ancient religions ,</segment>
		<segment id="14" parent="13" relname="adversative-concession">as far as the fragmentary nature of the surviving source material allows .</segment>
